{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "auth-system-collection",
    "name": "Auth System API",
    "description": "Complete authentication system API collection with Email/OTP verification\n\n## Setup Instructions\n\n1. **Configure MailTrap:**\n   - Sign up at https://mailtrap.io/\n   - Go to Sending > Integrations > NodeMailer\n   - Copy the credentials to .env file\n   - MAILTRAP_HOST: smtp.mailtrap.io\n   - MAILTRAP_PORT: 2525\n   - MAILTRAP_USER: your_username\n   - MAILTRAP_PASS: your_password\n\n2. **Start the Server:**\n   - npm install\n   - npm start (or npm run dev)\n\n3. **Run the Tests:**\n   - Register a new user\n   - Check MailTrap inbox for OTP email\n   - Verify OTP using the email received\n   - Login with verified account",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "Register",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Test 1: Check status code is 201",
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 201\", function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(201);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 2: Check success is true",
              "pm.test(\"Success is true\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql(true);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 3: Check message about OTP",
              "pm.test(\"Message mentions OTP sent\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.message).to.include(\"OTP sent\");",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 4: Check user object in response",
              "pm.test(\"User object exists with email\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.user).to.have.property('email');",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.user.isVerified).to.eql(false);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Save email to variable for next requests",
              "var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "pm.globals.set('test_email', jsonData.user.email);",
              "console.log('Registered email: ' + jsonData.user.email);"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"name\": \"Test User\",\n  \"email\": \"testuser@mailinator.com\",\n  \"phone\": \"9876543210\",\n  \"password\": \"TestPass123\",\n  \"confirmPassword\": \"TestPass123\"\n}"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:5000/api/auth/register",
          "protocol": "http",
          "host": ["localhost"],
          "port": "5000",
          "path": ["api", "auth", "register"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Verify OTP",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
              "// Test 1: Check status code is 200",
              "pm.test(\"Status code is 200\", function () {",
              "    pm.response.to.have.status(200);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 2: Check success is true",
              "pm.test(\"Success is true\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.success).to.eql(true);",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 3: Check message",
              "pm.test(\"Message is 'Email verified successfully'\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.message).to.include(\"verified\");",
              "});",
              "",
              "// Test 4: Check user is verified",
              "pm.test(\"User isVerified is true\", function () {",
              "    var jsonData = pm.response.json();",
              "    pm.expect(jsonData.user.isVerified).to.eql(true);",
              "});"
            ],
            "type": "text/javascript"
          }
        }
      ],
      "request": {
        "method": "POST",
        "header": [
          {
            "key": "Content-Type",
            "value": "application/json",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ],
        "body": {
          "mode": "raw",
          "raw": "{\n  \"email\": \"testuser@mailinator.com\",\n  \"otp\": \"123456\"\n}\n\n/* \n  IMPORTANT: Replace OTP with actual OTP received in email\n  1. After registering, check MailTrap inbox (https://mailtrap.io/)\n  2. Look for email with subject: \"Verify Your Account\"\n  3. Copy the 6-digit OTP from the email\n  4. Paste it in the OTP field above\n*/"
        },
        "url": {
          "raw": "http://localhost:5000/api/auth/verify-otp",
          "protocol": "http",
          "host": ["localhost"],
          "port": "5000",
          "path": ["api", "auth", "verify-otp"]
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "name": "Resend OTP",
      "event": [
        {
          "listen": "test",
          "script": {
            "exec": [
